, it also turns away from it and towards the compelling contributions of Haitian curators and artists to the decentralization of contemporary art.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aArt, Caribbean. 0aArt, Haitian. 0aIntersectionality (Sociology). 0aRacism in art. 4aAffect. 4aArt. 4aCaribbean. 4aCultural Anthropology. 4aCultural Studies. 4aDecoloniality. 4aHaiti. 4aInstallation Art. 4aIntersectionality. 4aMuseology. 4aMuseum. 4aPostcolonialism. 4aRacism. 4aSocially-engaged Art. 4aSouth American Art. 4aWhiteness. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aAffect.  aArt.  aCaribbean.  aCultural Anthropology.  aCultural Studies.  aDecoloniality.  aHaiti.  aInstallation Art.  aIntersectionality.  aMuseology.  aMuseum.  aPostcolonialism.  aRacism.  aSocially-engaged Art.  aSouth American Art.  aWhiteness.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP ROW Ebook Package English 2020z978311069630108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311068961740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978383945592040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839455920423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839455920/original  a978-3-11-068961-7  transcript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-069629-5  DG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2b2020  a978-3-11-069630-1  PP ROW Ebook Package English 2020b2020  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  aE